Citation.sTitle: Solubility of Dioxopromethazine Hydrochloride in Different Solvents
Citation.sAbstract: The solubilities of dioxopromethazine hydrochloride (DPZ) in water, acetic acid, ethanol, methanol, N,Ndimethylformamide, N-methyl ketopyrrolidide, and acetone between (278 and 328) K were measured using a laser monitoring observation technique. Results of these measurements were correlated with a semiempirical equation. For seven solvents studied, the data are well fitted with a semiempirical equation.
